data.title: Looking to 2020
data.description: Nine players, nine cities, and one goal. We sat down with players from all around the world and discussed how excited they are to be playing in their home cities for the 2020 Overwatch League season.

data.title: Tactics: How Surefour's Hanzo Shut Down the Los Angeles Valiant
data.description: The Los Angeles Valiant were battling the Los Angeles Gladiators on Volskaya Industries. The LA Valiant had to capture 80% of Point B with less than a minute remaining and they had a decent shot at doing it. However, Surefour dismantled the last two pushes of the Los Angeles Valiant. In this episode of Tactics, we break down just how Surefour managed to find those key headshots and how the Los Angeles Valiant failed to mitigate that risk for themselves! It’s all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: The Battle for LA 7 | Official Trailer
data.description: A fight for the City of Angels lies ahead…and this time, it’s personal! The Overwatch League brought in two big-shot Hollywood producers to make sure the seventh meeting of the Los Angeles Gladiators and the Los Angeles Valiant gets its due.

data.title: Re-Fusion: Philadelphia Swings for the Grand Finals
data.description: Watching London hold the trophy above their heads at the Inaugural season’s Grand Finals was tough for the Philadelphia Fusion. Poko, Carpe and EQO want to let the league know they won’t let history repeat itself and they intend to make it to the Grand Finals for their hometown crowd.

data.title: London Spitfire: Repeat Quest?
data.description: History was captured last year when the London Spitfire took home the Inaugural Season Overwatch League trophy. Can they re-capture history? They’ll have to fight out of the play-in bracket first.
